arguments.response_text: I've moved several times first for college then for work then for a different job and also in between for a few other reasons and you know each step seemed quite natural and only as I got older do I kind of piece together this narrative of wow that's a lot of movement you know how does that have an effect on my life overall and I think the interesting thing is that it felt so natural and easy and it almost expected because my parents are immigrants and they moved they left Greece in their like late teens early 20s to start a new life in America leaving a family behind and then we did visits when I was young so the idea of pursuing your goals through travel and felt natural and that's interesting
arguments.response_summary: The respondent discusses their frequent moves and how it felt natural, drawing parallels to their parents' immigration experience.
arguments.matched_prompt: How did you and your family build a life in Chicago?
